    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Describes the style and culture of the inhabitants of the Republic of Marshall Islands. The Marshall Islanders are recognized for the creation of the outrigger canoe. Originally, three forms of canoes were created: the walap, a sailing canoe with the capability of carrying up to 100 passengers; the tipnol, carrying up to 20 passengers; and the korkor, a small canoe to be used within a lagoon. Other artworks produced by the Marshall Islanders include woven or plaited products for the craft market or domestic use and various tattoo designs.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
